explanation:
os_status_string_t — Need the typedef/definition to know whether this is an array type (e.g. char[N]) or a char *; sizeof(*status_string) behaviour (buffer size vs pointer size) and null-termination assumptions depend on this.
osal_status_t — Type of the status parameter; inspect definition to confirm it is not a string alias or a type that could cause string comparisons inside OS_StatusToInteger.
OS_StatusToInteger — The only direct project function called that could itself call memcmp on null-terminated strings; its implementation must be checked for any memcmp usage on strings (indirect MISRA violation).
snprintf — The Standard Library function called to produce the string. Verify that it is used correctly (writes a terminating NUL, semantics w.r.t. size argument) and confirm whether the platform implementation uses memcmp on null-terminated strings (to rule out indirect violation).
memcmp — The MISRA-restricted function; include to search for any uses in OS_StatusToInteger, the snprintf implementation, or any other callees/utility stubs reachable from this function.
UT_Stub_RegisterReturnType, UT_Stub_RegisterContextWithMetaData, UT_ExecuteBasicHandler, UT_Stub_GetReturnValuePtr — These unit-test/stub-related callees appear in the static call graph for this function; include their implementations because test harness stubs or handlers reachable from the target could internally call memcmp on null-terminated strings, causing an indirect MISRA violation.
